    • Method Detail

      • get

        public final V get()
        Returns the required value of the property. If a metaproperty with a default value was used, such default value will be returned if the JSON object did not contain the property.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if there is no value.

      • orNull

        public final V orNull()
        Returns the loaded value of the property or null if there is no value. If a metaproperty with a default value was used, such default value will be returned if the JSON object did not contain the property.

      • or

        public final V or(@Nullable
   V defaultValue)
        Returns the loaded value of the property or the provided value if there is no value. If a metaproperty with a default value was used, such default value (instead of the provided one) will be returned if the JSON object did not contain the property.

      • getOptional

        public final Optional<V> getOptional()
        Returns the loaded value of the property as an Optional. If a metaproperty with a default value was used, such default value will be returned if the JSON object did not contain the property.
